  "A brewing company uses yeast to produce beer. The yeast converts sugars from barley malt into alcohol and carbon dioxide. Which metabolic pathway is responsible for the ethanol and CO₂ in the beer?": "",
  "Aerobic respiration in yeast mitochondria in most scenarios involving beer factors": "",
  "Glycolysis followed by alcoholic fermentation, in which pyruvate is decarboxylated to acetaldehyde (releasing CO₂) and then reduced to ethanol": "",
