  "Cancer cells have evolved a more efficient form of glycolysis, especially during periods of significant change": "",
  "Rapid glycolysis provides quick ATP and generates biosynthetic intermediates for rapid cell division; the speed advantage outweighs the lower ATP yield per glucose": "",
  "The Warburg effect: cancer cells use aerobic glycolysis because it produces ATP faster than oxidative phosphorylation and generates glycolytic intermediates (like G3P) that feed biosynthetic pathways needed for rapid growth and division.": "",
  "A biochemist adds a high concentration of ATP to a cell extract performing glycolysis and observes that the reaction rate decreases significantly. She then adds AMP and the rate increases. What enzyme is being regulated and how?": "",
