  "Glycolysis uses different enzymes in each organism, since the patterns governing glycolysis behavior generally combine with common conditions to create this type of result": "",
  "Glycolysis is the most conserved metabolic pathway across all domains of life. Its cytoplasmic location (no organelle needed), anaerobic nature, and universal conservation strongly suggest it arose in the last common ancestor of all living organisms on early, anoxic Earth.": "",
